## Account Warmup Schedule

### CRITICAL: Do NOT start outreach on Day 1. Build credibility first.

#### Week 1: Foundation (NO outreach)
- Complete all profile information
- Follow relevant accounts (founders, VCs, startup media)
- Like and engage with others' content (no self-promotion)
- Join relevant groups/communities
- Post 1-2 valuable, non-promotional posts

#### Week 2: Credibility Building (NO cold outreach)
- Post 3-4 valuable content pieces (fundraising tips, market insights)
- Engage in 10+ conversations daily (comments, replies)
- Follow 20-30 accounts per day
- Share others' content with thoughtful commentary
- Build follower base organically

#### Week 3: Soft Introduction (light outreach)
- Begin sharing PitchTok-related content (case studies, founder stories)
- Start answering fundraising questions in communities
- Engage with potential founders' content directly
- Queue first batch of DMs for approval (5/day max)

#### Week 4+: Full Operations
- Regular content publishing (per content calendar)
- Active comment monitoring and replies
- DM outreach at full daily limits
- Community participation

## Platform-Specific Warmup

### LinkedIn
- Week 1: 10 connections/day (people you actually know or relevant industry)
- Week 2: 15 connections/day + 3 comments on others' posts
- Week 3: 20 connections/day + 1 original post + 5 comments
- Week 4+: Full cadence (5 connection requests to cold leads, 3 posts/week)

### Twitter/X
- Week 1: Follow 30 accounts, like 20 tweets/day, reply to 5
- Week 2: 3 original tweets/day, reply to 10 tweets
- Week 3: 5 tweets/day, 1 thread/week, start DMs
- Week 4+: Full cadence

### å°çº¢ä¹¦
- Week 1: Follow 50 creators, save/like 30 posts/day
- Week 2: 2 posts (non-promotional, valuable content)
- Week 3: 3 posts/week, start engaging in comments
- Week 4+: Full cadence (3 content packs/week)

### Reddit
- Week 1: Subscribe to subreddits, upvote, read
- Week 2: Comment helpfully on 5 threads/day (NO self-promotion)
- Week 3: Post 1 valuable discussion, continue commenting
- Week 4+: Regular participation + occasional PitchTok mentions when relevant
- NEVER spam â€” Reddit users will destroy your reputation

